1977;;Grayeagle;;American;;Charles B. Pierce;;Ben Johnson, Lana Wood;;western;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grayeagle;;Set in 1848, in the Montana Territory, Ben Johnson plays John Coulter who lives on the plains with his daughter Beth and his friend Standing Bear. The story is told mainly from a Native American point of view.<br><br>Beth is kidnapped by Greyeagle of the Cheyenne nation, who was tasked by the nation's chief to bring Beth to him. Coulter and Standing Bear go through various adventures to find Beth, to bring her back safely home.